About this item

  • Perfectly Matte: Achieving a flawless, color-intense matte finish is just a swipe away with Maybelline Super Stay Matte Ink liquid matte lipstick. Get up to 16 hours of wear with this liquid lipstick in shade Lover for a mid-tone mauve pink lip color
  • Iconic Longwear Formula: The long lasting formula of this highly pigmented liquid lipstick gives you super saturated color in a smudge-free, matte finish. Color locks in, feels and looks fresh all day, with no transfer
  • Sculpt With Precision: Get effortless, smooth application every time with the unique arrow applicator. This matte lipstick glides on easily for comfortable all-day wear. Removes easily with Maybelline Super Stay Eraser lipstick remover
  • Create any look with Maybelline; foundation, BB creams, concealers, and setting powders for the perfect canvas, eye shadows, mascara, brow pencils, and eyeliners for any eye look and lip products, from showstopping lipstick to plumping lip gloss

Product Description

Ink your lips in up to 16 hours saturated liquid matte. SuperStay Matte Ink features a unique arrow applicator for precise application and is available in a range of super saturated shades. Up to 16 hours saturated matte, Highly-pigmented color, Long-lasting, saturated matte, Available in a collection of in10se saturated shades Step 1. Apply liquid lipstick in the center of your upper lip and follow the contours of your mouth. Step 2. Glide the liquid lipstick across the entire bottom lip. Step 3. Allow product to dry. CAUTION: FLAMMABLE UNTIL DRY. DO NOT USE NEAR FIRE, FLAME, OR HEAT.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Smooth Matte Finish
The pictures are 4 hours after applying. I got the Globe one. It is thick going on so I have to blot but absolutely love the matte finish!! It does not smear or transfer to cups or to my partner after a kiss. I love it. However if you notice it does not stay on the back side of the lip where the lip it slightly wet. If you do get lips wet while drinking or eating then it will come off. I have had this for about a week and wear it every day. Typically last around 6-7 hours!! I would give a 5 star but because it doesn’t stay on the back side of lip and gives a line where it stops I am only giving it a 4.

5.0 out of 5 stars Long wear gentle on lips, compatible with Mac lipglass
Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
Color: 15 LOVERSize: 1 Count (Pack of 1)Verified Purchase
I am really hooked on this lipstick! It's very long wearing and it's super gentle on my lips. I've tried long wear lipstick in the past and found that it dried my lips out too much and irritated them, like it sucked the moisture out of my lips. This doesn't do that at all! They feel very comfortable underneath, no itching, and don't feel dry when I take it off at the end of the day. It has a really pretty matte sheen, and I like the scent, kind of vanilla.

Let me address some common complaints among other reviewers and why I think they're wrong. First off, it is really easy to take off if you know what you're doing. Oil takes this stuff off quite easily, so do some makeup wipes. Most lip balms will take it off as well. For example, I use laneige lip balm at night and it takes it off just fine. Put some on, rub your lips together, and then wipe off with a tissue. Neutrogena makeup wipes also take it off.

Secondly, I do agree that this product is very sticky. I have found that I can put my Mac lipglass on over top and now it's not sticky anymore! Also the gloss gives it a nice sheen or glitter depending on what shade of gloss. And most importantly, Mac lipglass does not take it off, yay!

Third, because oil takes it off, depending on what you had to eat, it will or won't survive your meal. So some people say they had really good luck with it lasting all day, and other people complaining that it's worn off after a few hours. I think it really depends on what you had to eat that day. If I have something light and non-greasy for lunch like sushi then my lipstick lasts the entire work day without needing a touch-up. If I have a lunch that's heavy on oil, like salad dressing or a lot of butter, then I have to reapply after I finish eating. But one touch up in the middle of the day to freshen up the center of your lips is no big deal! That still wayyyyy beats any kind of conventional lipstick.

Fourth, your lips need to be totally clean and oil free before you apply. And this stuff takes about a minute to set. So if you're putting it on, say, on top of lip balm, it isn't going to be long wear lipstick. Likewise, let it set well before you go off for the day. If I get lipstick on my teeth, it's usually during this period where it hasn't set yet. If that happens, I just wait until it is set, and then wipe it off my teeth with a Kleenex. Not a big deal at all!

Now on to the colors... I am extremely fair skinned (usually the lightest color in any foundation brand), blue eyes, cool undertone, and brown/ reddish hair. On me, I really like the way dreamer and lover look. Very flattering and works well if you have cool undertones in your skin. I like poet, but it's almost a little too orange/ coral for my skin tone. I agree with other reviewers that seductress doesn't look at all like the photos online. That shade is way more brown in person. Like a '90s brown... I'll probably wear it some, but definitely not the most flattering for cool toned skin. I definitely plan on buying another color or two. At this price point, it's pretty easy to experiment. Do yourself a favor and give it a try!

Ashley
5.0 out of 5 stars Gotta collect them all!
Reviewed in the United States on October 23, 2020
Color: 65 SEDUCTRESSSize: 0.17 Fl Oz (Pack of 1)Verified Purchase
These are my absolute favorite lipsticks of all time. They stay on all day, last through meals, stay on all night when I go to bed forgetting to take it off, and they’re super affordable. (Dare I say these may last longer than the Stila liquid lipsticks, which I also love.) I got kind of obsessed with finding the right shade for my wedding day someday that I bought 10 in one summer. Not my proudest moment, but I’ve really enjoyed them. No regrets, even though I don’t love every color.

My absolute favorites are Seductress, Revolutionary, Inspirer and Voyager.

My least favorites are the fair skin colored ones, like Loyalist and Poet. They’re too close to my skin color which looked gross on me in bathroom lighting. Out of the two I’m more likely to wear Poet. Dreamer is like a Pepto Bismol color. Founder is like a pinkish red, like the color of my shirt. Pathfinder was a lighter, pinker red and hard for me to match. Seductress is AMAZING, especially on redheads. An awesome casual color.

I’ve added pictures of every color I bought along with including their names in the photos. Each photo is taken either in front of a window or outside in order to use natural lighting to get an accurate shot of their true color. I’m hoping they’re helpful to you all.

I will say these lipsticks are super sticky, even after they dry. Licking them does not fix the sticky feeling. However, applying a super thin coat of chapstick by dabbing (not rubbing) the chapstick on the lower lip then pressing your lips together works perfectly! Just remember a little goes a LONG way, because if you add too much, the lipstick will start to come off. Maybelline’s Super Stay 24 Color lipsticks are very similar AND they each contain a chapstick on the opposite end of the lipstick. I left a review with pictures there because OBSESSED.

If I were to pick one of these colors for my wedding day next year, it would probably be Revolutionary.

To take them off without makeup wipes, apply a heavy layer of chapstick overtop and rub off with a tissue a few times.

I am not one to write reviews, but after my experience with this lipstick, I would be a fool not to write one.

Firstly, I purchased this to go with my Halloween costume but wanted to give it a try before then. Unsuspectingly I put it on, expecting it stays as the name says, but not to the staying power I received in my bottle.

I put on this magic a couple hours before bed, husband noticed and one thing led to another - shot caller is an excellent colour for the nights you want to call the shots or take the shots. It has ridickulous staying power.
10 stars, you go Maybelline.
